This paper deals with the recognition of languages in NL using finite automata, which falls under the category of formal languages (cs.FL). It also involves the analysis of error probabilities and randomness, which could be classified under computational complexity (cs.CC) and information theory (cs.IT). The concept of windable heads is a structural property of the automata, which could be related to the study of data structures (cs.DS) and logic (cs.LO).
